WEBVTT

00:02:32.132 --> 00:02:33.092
Han Seol-ah?

00:04:08.729 --> 00:04:10.022
That woman killed her.

00:04:10.773 --> 00:04:11.774
It was Han Seol-ah.

00:04:12.858 --> 00:04:14.401
I saw everything.

00:04:15.194 --> 00:04:16.403
That night,

00:04:16.487 --> 00:04:18.655
I went to the archive after the event

00:04:18.739 --> 00:04:19.990
to organize the catalogs.

00:04:21.700 --> 00:04:23.952
I waited a long time for the elevator,
but it didn't come,

00:04:24.036 --> 00:04:25.662
so I decided to take the stairs.

00:04:30.334 --> 00:04:33.128
Then I saw Han Seol-ah
rushing down the stairs from the rooftop,

00:04:34.129 --> 00:04:35.589
like someone trying to run away.

00:04:37.299 --> 00:04:39.384
I thought it was strange…

00:04:41.595 --> 00:04:43.180
until I went outside

00:04:44.515 --> 00:04:46.725
and found out someone had fallen
to their death from the rooftop.

00:04:50.521 --> 00:04:51.980
I know she did it.

00:04:55.025 --> 00:04:57.361
Why did you try to hide your identity?

00:04:59.113 --> 00:04:59.947
Because I was scared.

00:05:00.948 --> 00:05:02.199
If she finds out I provided the tip,

00:05:02.282 --> 00:05:03.784
she'll come after me.

00:05:04.785 --> 00:05:08.747
And I was worried my brother
might end up like all the other men.

00:05:10.082 --> 00:05:12.084
He used to be an underwater photographer,

00:05:12.167 --> 00:05:13.919
but now he just shoots events
at the auction house.

00:05:15.003 --> 00:05:18.340
Han Seol-ah manipulates
everyone around her.

00:05:27.808 --> 00:05:28.892
What are you trying to say?

00:05:30.686 --> 00:05:31.520
I'm curious.

00:05:31.603 --> 00:05:32.855
You've seen this video, right?

00:05:34.189 --> 00:05:35.065
Yes.

00:05:35.649 --> 00:05:37.192
Do you know who recorded it?

00:05:37.776 --> 00:05:38.652
No, I don't.

00:05:41.321 --> 00:05:42.239
It wasn't me.

00:05:44.158 --> 00:05:46.827
You were part of the Auction Team staff
that night, right?

00:05:46.910 --> 00:05:49.037
I was setting up for the auction
the whole time.

00:05:50.164 --> 00:05:51.874
If you don't believe me,
go through my phone.

00:06:05.262 --> 00:06:06.513
The statement she gave

00:06:06.597 --> 00:06:09.099
aligns with Han Seol-ah's movements
caught on CCTV.

00:06:10.142 --> 00:06:12.227
She followed Kim Yun-ji to the rooftop.

00:06:13.145 --> 00:06:16.231
Is Han Seol-ah a suspect now?

00:06:42.591 --> 00:06:44.843
CHARITY AUCTION TO SUPPORT EMERGING
ARTISTS IN PARTNERSHIP WITH TAEMYUNG

00:06:52.309 --> 00:06:53.727
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:07:18.627 --> 00:07:20.796
Can we talk? It'll only take five minutes.

00:07:21.380 --> 00:07:22.631
I don't have time for that.

00:07:23.215 --> 00:07:24.424
The event is about to start.

00:07:25.259 --> 00:07:27.469
Didn't it ever occur to you
that Kim Yun-ji knew too much?

00:07:29.888 --> 00:07:32.724
How did she meet Yoon Seung-jae
and find out about the policy?

00:07:33.684 --> 00:07:34.601
Don't you want to know?

00:07:41.358 --> 00:07:44.569
Does knowing that change anything?

00:07:57.332 --> 00:08:01.670
The next lot is
The Abyss by Kim Seung-min.

00:08:02.379 --> 00:08:05.173
We'll open at 850 million won
and take bids in 50 million increments.

00:08:06.341 --> 00:08:07.384
850 million?

00:08:08.010 --> 00:08:09.261
We have 850 million.

00:08:09.344 --> 00:08:11.888
Anyone at 900 million?

00:08:13.640 --> 00:08:15.267
900 million on the floor.

00:08:15.350 --> 00:08:16.476
950 million?

00:08:16.560 --> 00:08:19.062
At 950 million.

00:08:19.896 --> 00:08:21.273
We have 950 million.

00:08:21.857 --> 00:08:23.400
The next lot is

00:08:23.984 --> 00:08:27.279
Vanished Sensation by Fabien Leclerc.

00:08:27.362 --> 00:08:31.658
This emerging talent has been making waves
among European collectors.

00:08:33.327 --> 00:08:36.121
We'll open at 300 million won

00:08:36.204 --> 00:08:38.206
and take bids
in ten million won increments.

00:08:39.499 --> 00:08:40.500
300 million?

00:08:41.293 --> 00:08:42.336
We have 300 million.

00:08:42.419 --> 00:08:43.337
310 million?

00:08:43.837 --> 00:08:44.671
We have 310 million.

00:08:44.755 --> 00:08:46.214
320 million?

00:08:46.798 --> 00:08:48.216
We have 320 million.

00:08:48.300 --> 00:08:49.217
330 million?

00:08:50.135 --> 00:08:51.762
We have 330 million. 340 million?

00:08:52.304 --> 00:08:53.638
We have 340 million.

00:08:53.722 --> 00:08:54.556
350 million?

00:08:55.140 --> 00:08:56.892
We have 350 million.

00:08:56.975 --> 00:08:58.018
360 million?

00:09:01.188 --> 00:09:05.275
Among the lots in today's special auction,
I've set aside these five

00:09:05.359 --> 00:09:07.361
to show you privately, sir.

00:09:09.488 --> 00:09:11.531
Is this what you mentioned before?

00:09:11.615 --> 00:09:14.493
Overseas collectors
are already showing interest.

00:09:14.576 --> 00:09:15.786
Just like Stiller,

00:09:16.370 --> 00:09:22.000
these artists here, especially Leclerc,
are going to blow up soon.

00:09:22.751 --> 00:09:25.796
Whatever you suggest
is guaranteed to rise in value.

00:09:26.546 --> 00:09:29.466
It's not too late for Taemyung
to lock down these pieces.

00:09:29.549 --> 00:09:33.053
You'll see their value increase tenfold
within the next several years.

00:09:33.637 --> 00:09:37.224
The Taemyung Cultural Foundation
is about to open a center in Busan.

00:09:37.307 --> 00:09:39.476
You should stock it
with lucrative artwork.

00:09:42.354 --> 00:09:43.522
Tenfold, you say?

00:09:43.605 --> 00:09:47.192
So I suppose it's in my best interest
to win the bids at any cost.

00:09:47.818 --> 00:09:52.197
When have I ever made a suggestion
that wasn't in your best interest?

00:09:55.033 --> 00:09:56.368
1.45 billion won.

00:09:57.452 --> 00:10:00.288
Anyone at 1.45 billion? 1.45 billion.

00:10:00.372 --> 00:10:03.583
We have 1.45 billion.

00:10:04.167 --> 00:10:05.627
1.46 billion?

00:10:06.211 --> 00:10:07.212
At 1.46 billion.

00:10:07.921 --> 00:10:10.132
We have 1.46 billion.

00:10:10.799 --> 00:10:12.259
1.47 billion?

00:10:15.762 --> 00:10:17.639
We have 1.47 billion.

00:10:18.390 --> 00:10:21.935
This special auction is for a good cause,
so the competition seems to be heating up.

00:10:22.686 --> 00:10:24.604
Anyone at 1.48 billion?

00:10:25.397 --> 00:10:26.731
1.48 billion.

00:10:27.941 --> 00:10:29.401
We have 1.48 billion.

00:10:29.484 --> 00:10:31.069
1.49 billion?

00:10:34.030 --> 00:10:36.116
Anyone at 1.49 billion?

00:10:36.908 --> 00:10:38.076
1.49 billion?

00:10:39.453 --> 00:10:42.247
We have 1.49 billion won.
This is the highest bid so far.

00:10:43.415 --> 00:10:46.084
Do we have anyone at 1.5 billion?

00:10:46.793 --> 00:10:47.794
1.5 billion?

00:10:48.295 --> 00:10:50.797
Anyone at 1.5 billion?

00:10:57.929 --> 00:11:00.807
We have 1.5 billion.

00:11:02.309 --> 00:11:04.269
Anyone at 1.51 billion?

00:11:05.228 --> 00:11:08.273
I'll call for 1.51 billion again

00:11:08.356 --> 00:11:09.566
before closing the bidding.

00:11:10.567 --> 00:11:11.485
1.51 billion?

00:11:12.235 --> 00:11:13.361
1.51 billion?

00:11:13.987 --> 00:11:15.363
1.51 billion.

00:11:17.657 --> 00:11:18.617
Sold!

00:11:19.242 --> 00:11:21.703
Vanished Sensation by Fabien Leclerc

00:11:21.786 --> 00:11:24.498
has been sold to Chairman Park Min-cheol
of Taemyung Group.

00:11:25.874 --> 00:11:28.460
A portion of today's auction proceeds

00:11:28.543 --> 00:11:31.880
will go toward supporting
emerging artists.

00:11:31.963 --> 00:11:33.131
Thank you.

00:11:50.232 --> 00:11:51.566
Ms. Han Seol-ah.

00:11:51.650 --> 00:11:53.652
Please come with us to the police station.

00:12:02.118 --> 00:12:03.912
I'm on the clock. What is this about?

00:12:03.995 --> 00:12:06.456
We're asking you
to come with us voluntarily.

00:12:10.460 --> 00:12:11.836
I refuse to comply.

00:12:13.255 --> 00:12:15.298
Then, as of now,

00:12:15.382 --> 00:12:18.510
you're under arrest
as a suspect in the murder of Kim Yun-ji.

00:12:20.512 --> 00:12:21.555
You have the right to remain silent.

00:12:21.638 --> 00:12:24.140
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

00:12:24.724 --> 00:12:26.601
You have the right to an attorney.

00:12:28.562 --> 00:12:29.396
Let's go.

00:13:08.852 --> 00:13:10.812
Didn't it ever occur to you
that Kim Yun-ji knew too much?

00:13:12.063 --> 00:13:14.858
How did she meet Yoon Seung-jae
and find out about the policy?

00:13:15.650 --> 00:13:16.985
Don't you want to know?

00:13:17.569 --> 00:13:21.156
Does knowing that change anything?

00:13:22.032 --> 00:13:22.907
Eun-hyuk.

00:13:23.742 --> 00:13:24.951
Eun-hyuk!

00:13:26.328 --> 00:13:27.537
Eun-hyuk!

00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:30.874
Don't go.

00:13:31.625 --> 00:13:33.376
What can you possibly do there?

00:13:33.460 --> 00:13:34.628
Why are you doing this to Seol-ah?

00:13:34.711 --> 00:13:35.920
Why?

00:13:36.004 --> 00:13:38.715
I just told them what I saw and know.

00:13:38.798 --> 00:13:40.258
The truth has to come out!

00:13:40.342 --> 00:13:41.885
Why didn't you tell me?

00:13:42.469 --> 00:13:43.386
What if I had?

00:13:43.887 --> 00:13:44.929
Would you have believed me?

00:13:48.933 --> 00:13:49.934
Move.

00:13:55.940 --> 00:13:56.858
Eun-hyuk.

00:13:56.941 --> 00:13:58.193
Hey, Do Eun-hyuk!

00:14:10.789 --> 00:14:11.998
Hey, did you unlock it?

00:14:13.291 --> 00:14:16.086
Come on now, they don't call me
Yongsan's Dr. Shin for no reason.

00:14:16.169 --> 00:14:17.796
I may not have money,
but I do have skills.

00:14:20.298 --> 00:14:21.174
Jeez.

00:14:21.257 --> 00:14:23.677
Who's the insane owner
of this burner phone?

00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:25.512
They installed a spy app on it.

00:14:26.096 --> 00:14:27.263
-A spy app?
-Yes.

00:14:27.347 --> 00:14:30.433
It's a stealth app
that records calls and surrounding audio.

00:14:30.517 --> 00:14:32.227
It's pretty expensive,

00:14:32.310 --> 00:14:33.645
and you have to pay monthly fees.

00:14:34.437 --> 00:14:35.480
Does it still work?

00:14:35.563 --> 00:14:36.898
Just a sec.

00:14:36.981 --> 00:14:39.693
AUDIO FILE LIST

00:14:39.776 --> 00:14:41.945
It uses fingerprint recognition,
so I don't think so.

00:14:43.405 --> 00:14:44.823
It doesn't work,

00:14:44.906 --> 00:14:47.242
but whatever was saved are audio files,
so I'll try to unlock it.

00:14:47.325 --> 00:14:48.451
PLACE YOUR FINGER ON THE HOME BUTTON
TO VERIFY YOUR IDENTITY

00:14:48.535 --> 00:14:49.744
Hurry up and send them to me.

00:14:50.412 --> 00:14:52.956
How about if you hurry up
and get a new phone instead?

00:14:53.039 --> 00:14:53.957
I'm hanging up.

00:15:02.132 --> 00:15:04.259
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:15:08.596 --> 00:15:09.514
Ms. Han Seol-ah.

00:15:11.099 --> 00:15:13.101
You gave a false statement
during the witness interview

00:15:13.184 --> 00:15:14.853
and refused to accompany us
for questioning, right?

00:15:16.604 --> 00:15:17.814
This is the result of all that.

00:15:17.897 --> 00:15:18.773
From now on,

00:15:19.983 --> 00:15:21.568
think carefully before you answer.

00:15:21.651 --> 00:15:23.570
Think about the consequences

00:15:24.320 --> 00:15:25.739
of the statement you make
from here on out.

00:15:49.679 --> 00:15:51.431
I'll ask you again.

00:15:51.514 --> 00:15:53.641
When did you last see Ms. Kim Yun-ji?

00:15:54.642 --> 00:15:56.519
In the dressing room after the party.

00:15:57.896 --> 00:15:59.731
Why didn't you mention your argument?

00:16:01.649 --> 00:16:04.861
Were you planning to keep that a secret
if the video hadn't spread online?

00:16:08.740 --> 00:16:10.533
Where were you
at the time of the incident?

00:16:10.617 --> 00:16:13.703
Last time, you said
you were in the Auction Team office.

00:16:14.579 --> 00:16:15.955
Is your answer still the same?

00:16:18.416 --> 00:16:19.292
I'm not sure.

00:16:25.673 --> 00:16:27.967
Is she trying to test us?

00:16:35.892 --> 00:16:37.268
At 21:58,

00:16:37.852 --> 00:16:41.731
Ms. Kim Yun-ji got off on the 12th floor
and went to the rooftop to vape.

00:16:46.027 --> 00:16:47.487
At 22:02,

00:16:48.112 --> 00:16:51.699
you followed her
and got off on the 12th floor.

00:16:53.284 --> 00:16:55.745
About 9 minutes later, at 22:11,

00:16:55.829 --> 00:16:58.081
Ms. Kim Yun-ji fell to her death
from the rooftop.

00:16:59.999 --> 00:17:01.626
We have a witness.

00:17:01.709 --> 00:17:05.463
They saw you running away
from the rooftop.

00:17:06.798 --> 00:17:08.049
Just confess now.

00:17:08.633 --> 00:17:10.718
Where were you
at the time of the incident?

00:17:17.308 --> 00:17:18.142
You're right.

00:17:19.269 --> 00:17:23.106
That night, I went to the 12th floor
and up to the rooftop to find Ms. Kim.

00:17:25.024 --> 00:17:27.735
I didn't mention it because I was afraid
it might cause a misunderstanding.

00:17:35.869 --> 00:17:38.371
But by the time I reached the rooftop,

00:17:39.789 --> 00:17:42.709
Ms. Kim had already taken her life.

00:17:47.338 --> 00:17:48.882
I was scared.

00:17:52.260 --> 00:17:54.053
And I wanted to get out of there.

00:17:54.137 --> 00:17:55.179
That's all.

00:17:57.724 --> 00:17:59.976
Ms. Kim was already dead,

00:18:01.102 --> 00:18:04.105
and my statement
wouldn't have changed anything.

00:18:05.356 --> 00:18:08.401
Don't most people call 119
in such a situation?

00:18:09.235 --> 00:18:11.988
They don't run away
and lie about not having been there

00:18:12.071 --> 00:18:13.239
like you did.

00:18:14.782 --> 00:18:15.909
So are you saying…

00:18:17.869 --> 00:18:20.788
that's evidence I killed Ms. Kim?

00:18:22.707 --> 00:18:23.958
Look, Ms. Han Seol-ah.

00:18:24.042 --> 00:18:27.629
You assume you have the upper hand
because there's no direct evidence.

00:18:28.212 --> 00:18:30.089
But there's an autopsy report
suggesting the possibility of murder,

00:18:30.173 --> 00:18:31.841
along with CCTV footage and a witness.

00:18:31.925 --> 00:18:35.637
Given this much circumstantial evidence,
even a judge can't rule it out.

00:18:38.932 --> 00:18:39.891
Let me make this clear.

00:18:41.351 --> 00:18:42.852
You're not getting out of this

00:18:43.978 --> 00:18:45.021
unless you have a solid alibi.

00:19:05.875 --> 00:19:07.752
ROYAL AUCTION CHIEF AUCTIONEER
ARRESTED ON MURDER CHARGES

00:19:11.673 --> 00:19:16.678
YOUR HOME
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

00:19:16.761 --> 00:19:20.932
ROYAL AUCTION CHIEF AUCTIONEER
ARRESTED ON MURDER CHARGES

00:19:21.015 --> 00:19:24.727
GANGHA POLICE ARREST ART AUCTIONEER MS. A
ON CHARGES OF MURDERING HER COLLEAGUE

00:19:31.317 --> 00:19:33.361
MS. B WAS FOUND DEAD
AFTER FALLING FROM THE COMPANY'S ROOFTOP

00:19:33.444 --> 00:19:35.530
MS. A HAS BEEN NAMED THE PRIMARY SUSPECT

00:19:43.746 --> 00:19:47.417
VISITATION ROOM

00:20:08.646 --> 00:20:11.482
You've done nothing wrong,
so it's going to be okay.

00:20:15.987 --> 00:20:18.031
Just because you were in the same place
doesn't mean they can--

00:20:18.114 --> 00:20:19.365
Is Eun-hye the witness?

00:20:26.789 --> 00:20:28.166
I believe you.

00:20:28.833 --> 00:20:30.043
You know that, right?

00:20:31.002 --> 00:20:32.879
I'll do whatever I can to help you.

00:20:35.548 --> 00:20:36.716
Think it over again.

00:20:36.799 --> 00:20:39.677
Did you see anyone at that time?

00:20:56.152 --> 00:20:58.780
You know it's illegal to record
outside the interrogation room, right?

00:21:00.073 --> 00:21:01.365
The sister is the tip caller,

00:21:01.949 --> 00:21:03.201
and the brother is the helper.

00:21:05.912 --> 00:21:07.038
How interesting.

00:21:07.121 --> 00:21:09.373
What are they saying?

00:21:09.957 --> 00:21:11.584
Was there anything else
in the studio apartment?

00:21:17.965 --> 00:21:18.800
No.

00:21:25.473 --> 00:21:28.142
Maybe she found out
Kim Yun-ji was stalking her

00:21:28.226 --> 00:21:29.560
and got into a fight.

00:21:32.146 --> 00:21:34.982
We just need
that one decisive piece of evidence.

00:21:38.694 --> 00:21:39.946
Hey, Woo-seok.

00:21:40.696 --> 00:21:41.697
When did you get here?

00:21:41.781 --> 00:21:42.615
How've you been?

00:21:43.282 --> 00:21:44.450
You want to join us?

00:21:44.534 --> 00:21:45.785
The captain isn't here.

00:21:54.502 --> 00:21:55.461
What are you doing here?

00:21:58.548 --> 00:22:01.342
I heard you needed the insurance files
for the deceased men.

00:22:03.594 --> 00:22:05.930
It's not too late to back out
if you can't handle it.

00:22:06.889 --> 00:22:08.724
I hate being stabbed in the back, you see.

00:22:10.017 --> 00:22:11.894
Who asks for a favor so rudely?

00:22:11.978 --> 00:22:15.148
A favor is something you ask for
from someone who has more info than you.

00:22:19.986 --> 00:22:22.196
I'll decide
whether to reinvestigate or not.

00:22:23.781 --> 00:22:25.074
If you're done, get the hell out.

00:22:28.369 --> 00:22:29.787
It's been over 12 hours already.

00:22:30.788 --> 00:22:32.373
You sure you can get a warrant
at this rate?

00:22:36.085 --> 00:22:36.919
Hey.

00:22:37.962 --> 00:22:38.838
Are you crazy?

00:22:38.921 --> 00:22:40.339
You made the arrest,

00:22:41.674 --> 00:22:43.134
so make sure to see it through.

00:23:01.444 --> 00:23:02.737
I'm sorry.

00:23:02.820 --> 00:23:03.946
Here…

00:23:06.866 --> 00:23:08.534
It's been a while, Soo-yeon.

00:23:09.243 --> 00:23:11.287
What brings you here?

00:23:13.873 --> 00:23:16.250
Am I not allowed to come here?

00:23:17.043 --> 00:23:18.711
Oh, I didn't mean it that way.

00:23:30.681 --> 00:23:31.641
When did you get here?

00:23:31.724 --> 00:23:32.808
Just now.

00:23:33.309 --> 00:23:34.644
I brought you some underwear.

00:23:36.020 --> 00:23:36.896
Don't mind him.

00:23:37.813 --> 00:23:39.398
He's here on a different insurance case.

00:24:28.030 --> 00:24:28.864
Looking for this?

00:24:33.202 --> 00:24:35.538
I'm guessing Han Seol-ah
passed by here that night

00:24:36.122 --> 00:24:38.833
and asked someone to get rid of evidence
she'd overlooked.

00:24:39.959 --> 00:24:41.377
That someone being Do Eun-hyuk,
her helper.

00:24:44.380 --> 00:24:45.673
How did you know to come here?

00:24:48.467 --> 00:24:50.511
Good question. How did I know?

00:24:52.013 --> 00:24:54.682
I barely managed to ask the call center's
sign language interpreter for help.

00:24:54.765 --> 00:24:58.269
They sent me the lip-reading via text,
so take a look.

00:24:58.352 --> 00:24:59.186
Okay.

00:25:00.896 --> 00:25:02.815
AHN YOUNG-SOO

00:25:03.649 --> 00:25:05.860
"Check the monitor
in the exhibition room."

00:25:09.363 --> 00:25:11.198
Under Article 155 of the Criminal Act,

00:25:11.824 --> 00:25:13.993
a person who destructs,
conceals, or forges evidence

00:25:14.076 --> 00:25:18.164
will face up to five years of imprisonment
or a fine of up to seven million won.

00:25:20.916 --> 00:25:23.085
You've got guts, given how you could've
ended up as an accomplice.

00:25:24.253 --> 00:25:27.214
I came here to find out the truth too.

00:25:29.175 --> 00:25:30.968
I'm not going to protect Seol-ah
just because she's my friend.

00:25:31.635 --> 00:25:32.803
I want to help her

00:25:34.013 --> 00:25:35.264
because I trust her.

00:25:38.601 --> 00:25:40.269
Then let's find out…

00:25:43.064 --> 00:25:44.231
who she really is.

00:25:57.244 --> 00:25:58.371
What is it?

00:26:02.958 --> 00:26:06.087
She submitted footage of herself captured
in an art installation as an alibi.

00:26:07.880 --> 00:26:10.466
The metadata timestamps her at 22:11,

00:26:10.549 --> 00:26:13.094
which matches the time
when Kim Yun-ji fell.

00:26:37.034 --> 00:26:38.327
The higher-ups

00:26:38.911 --> 00:26:41.163
want us to close the Kim Yun-ji case
as a suicide

00:26:42.456 --> 00:26:43.833
and wrap it up quietly.

00:27:03.144 --> 00:27:05.020
Thank you for uncovering the truth.

00:27:06.021 --> 00:27:08.524
Did Kim Yun-ji seem like the type
to commit suicide?

00:27:10.526 --> 00:27:12.111
Is there really a "type" for such a thing?

00:27:13.946 --> 00:27:16.323
It's just one of those moments
when you have no other choice.

00:28:03.078 --> 00:28:03.954
FRAUDULENT & MISSING INPATIENT CASES

00:28:04.038 --> 00:28:04.872
Look.

00:28:05.372 --> 00:28:07.708
You deal with a case,
forget about it, and move on.

00:28:09.168 --> 00:28:10.002
You know,

00:28:10.085 --> 00:28:13.047
some people are cursed in a way
that brings harm or death to those nearby,

00:28:13.130 --> 00:28:14.840
like a deadly omen.

00:28:15.341 --> 00:28:17.092
Maybe that's the case with Han Seol-ah.

00:28:18.427 --> 00:28:19.637
It obviously can't be.

00:28:26.894 --> 00:28:28.312
What is it?

00:28:28.395 --> 00:28:29.980
Where are you off to now?

00:28:30.898 --> 00:28:34.527
I heard you walked out of there
before Attorney Kim even arrived.

00:28:37.738 --> 00:28:39.281
It was all thanks to you.

00:28:39.365 --> 00:28:40.783
Why do you say that?

00:28:41.659 --> 00:28:43.118
Because of Artist Hwang's
media art display.

00:28:43.202 --> 00:28:46.622
I was against it,
but you insisted that we bring it in.

00:28:46.705 --> 00:28:47.540
I guess you're right.

00:28:47.623 --> 00:28:48.457
Oh, no. I spilled it.

00:28:50.292 --> 00:28:51.293
Thanks.

00:28:52.211 --> 00:28:55.839
I didn't think you'd get out,
so I was going to bring this to you.

00:28:55.923 --> 00:28:56.757
Here.

00:28:57.299 --> 00:28:58.133
Take it with you.

00:28:58.884 --> 00:28:59.760
Thank you.

00:29:00.594 --> 00:29:03.097
You haven't been sleeping well, have you?

00:29:03.180 --> 00:29:05.683
Your eyes are so sunken.

00:29:05.766 --> 00:29:06.642
I'm sorry.

00:29:06.725 --> 00:29:08.269
I should have some coffee.

00:29:15.859 --> 00:29:17.069
Here.

00:29:17.820 --> 00:29:20.364
Spit it out if it's bitter,
but swallow it if it's sweet.

00:29:21.782 --> 00:29:25.536
Nobody rewards you
for tolerating something bitter.

00:29:31.792 --> 00:29:33.002
It's sweet, right?

00:29:33.502 --> 00:29:34.712
You'll feel better.

00:29:35.546 --> 00:29:36.380
Yes.

00:29:37.506 --> 00:29:38.507
Thank you.

00:29:41.594 --> 00:29:44.013
-Hey, over here!
-Here!

00:29:44.555 --> 00:29:45.514
-Come on!
-To the front!

00:29:45.598 --> 00:29:47.182
-Block him.
-Keep going!

00:29:47.266 --> 00:29:48.225
-Keep going!
-To the side.

00:29:48.309 --> 00:29:50.019
Nice! Steal the ball like I just did,
and pass.

00:29:50.603 --> 00:29:51.729
Take the ball.

00:29:51.812 --> 00:29:54.023
-Block him!
-Hey!

00:29:54.106 --> 00:29:55.357
And kick! Darn it!

00:29:55.941 --> 00:29:56.900
Kick it!

00:30:00.404 --> 00:30:02.698
Come on, louder!

00:30:02.781 --> 00:30:03.616
Yes!

00:30:06.243 --> 00:30:07.453
-Look at you.
-Sir.

00:30:08.621 --> 00:30:09.622
Running and everything.

00:30:14.001 --> 00:30:15.669
TRACKING REQUESTS WELCOME!
JUST CALL DR. SHIN

00:30:18.839 --> 00:30:20.674
Here's some water, sir.

00:30:21.342 --> 00:30:22.551
-Thanks.
-Enjoy.

00:30:25.638 --> 00:30:27.181
How do I sign up?

00:30:27.806 --> 00:30:28.641
-Oh, come on.
-Jeez.

00:30:28.724 --> 00:30:31.143
What is it now?
I did everything you asked!

00:30:31.226 --> 00:30:32.686
I'm serious.

00:30:33.270 --> 00:30:35.564
There's absolutely no way you can join.

00:30:35.648 --> 00:30:36.940
Why not?

00:30:37.024 --> 00:30:38.150
Because I'm the president of this club.

00:30:40.027 --> 00:30:41.195
Did you unlock the audio files?

00:30:42.029 --> 00:30:42.863
Oh, right.

00:30:43.489 --> 00:30:44.615
I only pulled the parts

00:30:45.574 --> 00:30:47.743
where Han Seol-ah's voice was recorded.

00:30:48.243 --> 00:30:49.411
-I just sent it to you.
-Okay.

00:30:51.747 --> 00:30:52.581
HAN SEOL-AH

00:30:53.415 --> 00:30:54.500
Nice work.

00:30:54.583 --> 00:30:55.793
You're leaving?

00:31:05.386 --> 00:31:07.888
"Affairs, ghosting, runaways"?

00:31:08.931 --> 00:31:10.182
EXPERIENCE ASSISTING INSURANCE COMPANY SIU

00:31:20.526 --> 00:31:21.694
-Run.
-Yes, sir.

00:31:24.196 --> 00:31:25.322
This is what you're doing now?

00:31:25.406 --> 00:31:28.784
It's just that people
don't get new phones these days, so--

00:31:28.867 --> 00:31:31.120
"Experience assisting
insurance company SIU."

00:31:31.829 --> 00:31:33.163
This is just unbelievable.

00:31:33.247 --> 00:31:34.206
What about it?

00:31:34.289 --> 00:31:36.750
It's a legitimate experience I gained
from being at your beck and call.

00:31:36.834 --> 00:31:37.668
Experience, my foot.

00:31:41.714 --> 00:31:43.132
I need you to find someone.

00:31:43.215 --> 00:31:45.759
Why is a former detective
asking me to find things all the time?

00:31:45.843 --> 00:31:46.969
His name is Ju Hyun-su.

00:31:47.594 --> 00:31:49.680
I have his details,
but he's not at the listed address,

00:31:49.763 --> 00:31:50.681
and he uses a burner phone.

00:31:50.764 --> 00:31:52.307
Oh, so he's a shady guy?

00:31:53.517 --> 00:31:55.853
-Give me his email address.
-Email?

00:31:55.936 --> 00:31:58.814
I don't know who he is,
but surely he orders in sometimes, no?

00:31:58.897 --> 00:32:02.067
These days, it's faster and more accurate
to go through delivery app brokers.

00:32:03.152 --> 00:32:04.278
Okay, I'll text it to you.

00:32:04.361 --> 00:32:05.904
Hey, find him as soon as possible.

00:32:05.988 --> 00:32:06.822
Okay.

00:32:07.823 --> 00:32:10.033
By the way,
can I get an advance or something?

00:32:11.201 --> 00:32:12.035
Right.

00:32:12.661 --> 00:32:14.163
-I'm counting on you.
-What's this?

00:32:14.747 --> 00:32:15.622
What's this?

00:32:18.792 --> 00:32:20.461
He works at an insurance company
that offers reimbursements,

00:32:20.544 --> 00:32:21.795
but he never reimburses me.

00:32:21.879 --> 00:32:23.714
I ought to reimburse him
with a slap in the face one day.

00:32:27.509 --> 00:32:29.553
HAN SEOL-AH RECORDINGS

00:32:29.636 --> 00:32:30.471
HAN SEOL-AH(1).M4A

00:32:30.554 --> 00:32:31.472
Hi, Suk-ji.

00:32:32.681 --> 00:32:34.433
I just got home.

00:32:35.934 --> 00:32:37.978
Okay, I'll stop by the bar tomorrow.

00:32:39.897 --> 00:32:41.440
HAN SEOL-AH(2).M4A

00:32:44.485 --> 00:32:45.319
Who is it?

00:32:46.195 --> 00:32:47.237
I'm from the management office.

00:32:52.993 --> 00:32:54.578
It's about the amendment
to the management regulations.

00:32:55.078 --> 00:32:56.079
Can you please cast your vote?

00:32:56.163 --> 00:32:57.331
You're the only one who hasn't.

00:32:57.915 --> 00:33:00.250
Oh, I've been coming home late from work.

00:33:00.334 --> 00:33:01.502
That's okay.

00:33:05.839 --> 00:33:08.217
This proposal is to convert
part of the storage room

00:33:08.300 --> 00:33:10.427
into a break room for the security staff.

00:33:11.512 --> 00:33:12.721
That's good to hear.

00:33:13.222 --> 00:33:16.892
It always bothered me seeing them eat
in a corner of the basement parking lot.

00:33:17.851 --> 00:33:19.853
I hope this makes things
a little more comfortable for them.

00:33:21.021 --> 00:33:22.147
Thank you.

00:33:22.231 --> 00:33:23.065
Have a good night.

00:33:23.732 --> 00:33:25.192
Thank you. Goodbye.

00:33:28.862 --> 00:33:30.948
She rented a studio apartment
and even spied on her.

00:33:32.574 --> 00:33:34.201
What was she trying to find out?

00:33:36.328 --> 00:33:37.579
Did she really choose…

00:33:38.664 --> 00:33:40.290
to take her own life?

00:34:05.190 --> 00:34:06.608
I thought it was rather strange

00:34:07.109 --> 00:34:09.611
when she left the TV station

00:34:09.695 --> 00:34:11.697
and suddenly decided to work
at an auction house.

00:34:12.447 --> 00:34:13.490
Do you know…

00:34:14.533 --> 00:34:16.827
the man Yun-ji was seeing?

00:34:17.786 --> 00:34:19.037
A man?

00:34:19.121 --> 00:34:21.498
PARKING PASS
ION MENTAL CLINIC

00:34:23.458 --> 00:34:24.751
SHOCK AS DOCTOR IN 30S DIES
IN SUSPECTED PROPOFOL SELF-INJECTION

00:34:27.629 --> 00:34:29.923
NFS REVEALS, "CAUSE OF DEATH WAS
PROPOFOL OVERDOSE, NO SIGNS OF FOUL PLAY"

00:34:30.757 --> 00:34:33.927
Dr. Choi was so head over heels for her
that he even dumped his girlfriend.

00:35:10.547 --> 00:35:12.674
Do you still struggle a lot
without medication?

00:35:13.926 --> 00:35:15.052
Yes.

00:35:15.135 --> 00:35:17.054
Considering
we're a family medicine clinic,

00:35:17.137 --> 00:35:19.014
we can't keep prescribing tranquilizers.

00:35:19.514 --> 00:35:21.266
Even for your own sake,

00:35:21.350 --> 00:35:23.894
maybe we should transfer you
to a mental clinic.

00:35:25.312 --> 00:35:26.146
No.

00:35:27.064 --> 00:35:29.316
It's the same as any hospital.

00:35:29.399 --> 00:35:31.234
-If you put aside your prejudice--
-It's not prejudice.

00:35:32.945 --> 00:35:33.862
It's from experience.

00:35:34.571 --> 00:35:35.739
ION MENTAL CLINIC
DIRECTOR CHOI YOUNG-HO

00:35:49.127 --> 00:35:50.128
One that I don't want to remember.

00:35:54.049 --> 00:35:56.176
I'll write you one more prescription.

00:35:56.885 --> 00:35:58.679
But I can't help you after this.

00:35:58.762 --> 00:36:02.349
NONORGANIC INSOMNIA

00:36:12.818 --> 00:36:15.988
Is this the woman
Dr. Choi Young-ho was seeing…

00:36:17.990 --> 00:36:19.199
before Han Seol-ah?

00:36:22.077 --> 00:36:22.911
How did you find out?

00:36:24.663 --> 00:36:26.331
You're pretty good.

00:36:29.835 --> 00:36:33.880
The information I have
is worth an omakase.

00:36:44.766 --> 00:36:46.309
I'll treat you again next time.

00:36:53.358 --> 00:36:55.485
She was a local TV anchor.

00:37:01.700 --> 00:37:02.701
What is she doing?

00:37:13.378 --> 00:37:14.421
What are you doing here?

00:37:15.130 --> 00:37:16.548
Sit down and eat with me.

00:37:18.258 --> 00:37:19.634
It's over between us.

00:37:19.718 --> 00:37:21.053
Just accept it.

00:37:21.136 --> 00:37:23.055
Let's not make it harder
than it needs to be.

00:37:27.893 --> 00:37:28.769
No.

00:37:30.145 --> 00:37:31.354
I can't end things this way.

00:37:33.857 --> 00:37:34.941
What if I die?

00:37:35.859 --> 00:37:38.153
Will you still break up with me
even if I die?

00:37:38.236 --> 00:37:39.362
Kim Yun-ji.

00:37:39.446 --> 00:37:40.530
Give that to me.

00:37:40.614 --> 00:37:42.491
What do you think you're doing?
Give it to me!

00:37:43.200 --> 00:37:44.576
Hand it over!

00:37:57.422 --> 00:38:00.175
It was absolute chaos.

00:38:05.347 --> 00:38:07.432
Apparently,
Dr. Choi just broke up with her

00:38:07.516 --> 00:38:09.267
soon after he started consultations
with Ms. Han.

00:38:10.977 --> 00:38:12.479
Was Han Seol-ah
unaware of their relationship?

00:38:13.105 --> 00:38:14.272
Probably not.

00:38:14.356 --> 00:38:17.234
Dr. Choi made sure to keep it a secret
because he was afraid of losing her.

00:38:17.818 --> 00:38:19.903
He liked her so much

00:38:19.986 --> 00:38:23.365
that he ended their official consultations
after just two months.

00:38:24.157 --> 00:38:25.408
What do you mean?

00:38:25.492 --> 00:38:27.160
In psychiatry,

00:38:27.244 --> 00:38:29.162
doctors are prohibited
from meeting with patients privately.

00:38:29.246 --> 00:38:32.415
So he had to make sure
she was no longer his patient.

00:38:32.999 --> 00:38:36.920
Countertransference is when a psychiatrist
develops strong feelings for a patient.

00:38:37.003 --> 00:38:37.963
It was one of those cases.

00:38:39.840 --> 00:38:40.757
Countertransference…

00:38:43.552 --> 00:38:44.469
But did you know

00:38:45.178 --> 00:38:48.140
many patients
also seduce their psychiatrist?

00:38:59.401 --> 00:39:00.569
Here.

00:39:04.531 --> 00:39:06.074
Please give that to Chair Kim.

00:39:06.741 --> 00:39:09.161
This exhibition was only possible
thanks to her.

00:39:10.996 --> 00:39:13.498
Okay, I'll deliver it to her myself.

00:39:13.582 --> 00:39:15.709
I'm sure she'll be delighted.

00:39:17.878 --> 00:39:20.380
The media is already showing
huge interest.

00:39:20.463 --> 00:39:22.716
The Leclerc piece in particular
is getting much attention.

00:39:23.216 --> 00:39:24.259
Just as I thought,

00:39:24.342 --> 00:39:26.219
trusting Chair Kim really paid off.

00:39:26.970 --> 00:39:30.515
I was surprised at how you secured
five bids that day.

00:39:31.558 --> 00:39:34.186
I guess someone gave you a tip beforehand.

00:39:35.979 --> 00:39:37.189
I did push it a bit,

00:39:37.272 --> 00:39:38.773
but they were Chair Kim's recommendations.

00:39:39.316 --> 00:39:41.943
In the end,
it was a worthwhile investment.

00:39:49.117 --> 00:39:51.953
He said the five lots he secured
during the special auction

00:39:52.037 --> 00:39:54.956
will be exhibited
at the Taemyung Art Center in Busan.

00:39:56.333 --> 00:39:57.375
Busan?

00:39:58.126 --> 00:39:59.211
Yes.

00:40:43.088 --> 00:40:44.547
What's the important thing
you wanted to tell me?

00:40:46.925 --> 00:40:48.885
You knew Kim Yun-ji
was stalking you, right?

00:40:52.389 --> 00:40:53.723
Do you know why?

00:40:56.351 --> 00:40:57.602
It wasn't because of Yoon Seung-jae.

00:40:58.395 --> 00:41:00.105
It was because of that psychiatrist,
Choi Young-ho.

00:41:03.358 --> 00:41:04.859
Before Choi Young-ho met you,

00:41:06.278 --> 00:41:07.529
he was Kim Yun-ji's man.

00:41:11.032 --> 00:41:12.909
She probably dreamed of a glamorous future

00:41:13.576 --> 00:41:15.370
as an anchor-doctor couple.

00:41:16.454 --> 00:41:18.748
But then you showed up
and took everything away from her.

00:41:19.332 --> 00:41:21.960
That's why she followed you
to Royal Auction.

00:41:24.254 --> 00:41:26.423
So she committed suicide because of him?

00:41:27.257 --> 00:41:28.258
I'm not sure.

00:41:28.341 --> 00:41:30.802
We still can't completely rule out
the possibility of murder.

00:41:32.846 --> 00:41:34.681
But what I'm really curious about

00:41:35.265 --> 00:41:37.684
is why those three men had to die.

00:41:39.936 --> 00:41:41.896
And what you gained from it.

00:41:51.614 --> 00:41:53.283
I'd like to ask that myself.

00:41:56.578 --> 00:41:58.705
What on earth did I gain from it?

00:42:02.208 --> 00:42:03.877
I didn't gain anything.

00:42:06.046 --> 00:42:07.255
I only lost.

00:42:29.569 --> 00:42:30.403
Ms. Han!

00:42:37.202 --> 00:42:40.080
Her blood test results show
a high level of benzodiazepines.

00:42:41.748 --> 00:42:44.209
It seems she took too many tranquilizers.

00:42:44.876 --> 00:42:46.211
Tranquilizers?

00:42:46.294 --> 00:42:48.296
She needs complete rest for the time being

00:42:48.380 --> 00:42:49.964
and should try to stop
taking her medication.

00:42:50.882 --> 00:42:51.883
Now, if you'll excuse me.

00:43:00.892 --> 00:43:02.310
You're Ms. Han Seol-ah's guardian, right?

00:43:04.479 --> 00:43:05.397
Oh, yes.

00:43:44.853 --> 00:43:47.021
TRIAGE STATION
ENTRY RESTRICTED TO THE PUBLIC

00:44:53.171 --> 00:44:54.255
Ms. Han Seol-ah?

00:44:59.552 --> 00:45:01.262
Mr. Paek asked me to escort you
to the conference room.

00:45:02.013 --> 00:45:03.765
Oh, sure.

00:45:19.239 --> 00:45:21.699
Welcome, Ms. Han.

00:45:23.368 --> 00:45:24.786
You don't look very well.

00:45:26.913 --> 00:45:28.581
Is it because
you've been through a lot lately?

00:45:30.458 --> 00:45:32.710
I considered sending my legal team,

00:45:33.795 --> 00:45:35.630
but you were released with no charges.

00:45:37.674 --> 00:45:39.884
Thank you for the thought.

00:45:40.969 --> 00:45:41.886
Not at all.

00:45:43.346 --> 00:45:44.180
Please take a seat.

00:45:52.605 --> 00:45:55.149
I reviewed the sales consignment proposal
you sent over.

00:45:55.692 --> 00:45:57.151
The terms are great.

00:45:57.235 --> 00:46:00.363
But why am I not tempted by this?

00:46:03.533 --> 00:46:06.536
Are you looking for anything
beyond profit?

00:46:07.120 --> 00:46:07.954
You know,

00:46:09.539 --> 00:46:11.749
I find myself being more attracted to
people than numbers lately.

00:46:11.833 --> 00:46:12.667
Especially…

00:46:14.460 --> 00:46:15.712
to people like you.

00:46:21.593 --> 00:46:23.720
It seems I misread you.

00:46:24.345 --> 00:46:27.056
I didn't expect someone
running a unicorn company

00:46:27.557 --> 00:46:30.518
to mix personal feelings with business.

00:46:32.020 --> 00:46:33.062
Men like that…

00:46:34.606 --> 00:46:36.482
aren't appealing to women.

00:46:38.568 --> 00:46:41.821
I don't do deals like this.
Please excuse me.

00:46:44.532 --> 00:46:45.867
If you leave like this,

00:46:45.950 --> 00:46:47.910
I'll come off as a pathetic guy.

00:46:51.122 --> 00:46:51.956
All right.

00:46:54.959 --> 00:46:57.003
We'll handle this matter
strictly as business.

00:47:03.509 --> 00:47:07.180
HAN SEOL-AH(34).M4A

00:47:07.263 --> 00:47:09.182
Suk-ji, can I get another drink?

00:47:10.516 --> 00:47:11.684
You've had enough.

00:47:13.394 --> 00:47:14.562
We're out of alcohol.

00:47:16.397 --> 00:47:17.440
You stubborn thing.

00:47:17.523 --> 00:47:19.108
Just cry it out.

00:47:19.192 --> 00:47:21.694
Even when you came to stay with me
after your parents passed,

00:47:21.778 --> 00:47:23.071
you only cried for a day.

00:47:24.572 --> 00:47:26.199
I couldn't believe you.

00:47:27.700 --> 00:47:29.619
Now I finally understand.

00:47:31.120 --> 00:47:32.872
You can't show your pain to anyone,

00:47:32.955 --> 00:47:34.791
so you bottle it all up,

00:47:34.874 --> 00:47:36.584
leaving you completely broken inside.

00:47:37.794 --> 00:47:38.628
Seol-ah.

00:47:40.505 --> 00:47:42.423
If you continue
to keep everything to yourself,

00:47:42.924 --> 00:47:45.218
you won't even know that you're in pain.

00:47:45.301 --> 00:47:46.803
You'll hold yourself together

00:47:47.595 --> 00:47:49.263
until one little thing
makes you fall apart.

00:47:51.057 --> 00:47:53.101
I don't have the right to fall apart.

00:47:55.395 --> 00:47:56.646
Because I survived…

00:47:59.607 --> 00:48:01.150
instead of my parents.

00:48:14.163 --> 00:48:14.997
Stop.

00:48:15.581 --> 00:48:17.041
A bit higher, please.

00:48:17.125 --> 00:48:18.334
Stop. That's good.

00:48:20.920 --> 00:48:23.172
Can you move the lights in a bit?

00:48:28.386 --> 00:48:29.345
Okay, next piece.

00:48:43.025 --> 00:48:44.277
Have you been working on
any projects lately?

00:48:45.778 --> 00:48:48.239
I have a private studio in my hometown.

00:48:49.866 --> 00:48:50.992
I go there on the weekends.

00:48:54.412 --> 00:48:55.872
What brings you here?

00:48:57.123 --> 00:49:00.084
I noticed you trust Han Seol-ah
more than you do your own sister.

00:49:01.544 --> 00:49:03.796
I was just wondering how that's possible.

00:49:04.964 --> 00:49:06.966
Have you never once suspected her?

00:49:09.135 --> 00:49:10.470
If I also suspect her,

00:49:11.471 --> 00:49:13.514
Seol-ah will be completely alone
in this world.

00:49:15.099 --> 00:49:16.476
Completely alone, huh?

00:49:18.227 --> 00:49:21.314
Only a soulmate could say
something like that so confidently.

00:49:25.485 --> 00:49:28.321
Then you must know what happened

00:49:28.946 --> 00:49:29.906
to Ms. Han Seol-ah's family.

00:49:33.242 --> 00:49:34.535
Should I just go ask her?

00:49:39.540 --> 00:49:42.460
They died in an accident
when we were 15 years old.

00:49:44.003 --> 00:49:45.046
What kind of accident?

00:49:45.797 --> 00:49:46.672
Seol-ah…

00:49:48.257 --> 00:49:50.510
lost her parents at a young age
and had a hard life.

00:49:51.469 --> 00:49:53.262
Please stop reopening old wounds.

00:49:53.346 --> 00:49:56.724
It can feel as painful as getting stabbed
for the person involved.

00:49:58.768 --> 00:49:59.727
Yes, I know.

00:50:01.229 --> 00:50:03.564
That's why I'm being careful
and asking you instead.

00:50:04.148 --> 00:50:06.567
It happened a long time ago, and it has
nothing to do with your investigation,

00:50:06.651 --> 00:50:07.735
so please stop.

00:50:08.945 --> 00:50:10.238
A fire broke out in their house.

00:50:14.367 --> 00:50:17.370
It was widely known as
the Cheongun family fire fatality case.

00:50:17.954 --> 00:50:20.206
Han Seol-ah was the only one who survived.

00:50:20.289 --> 00:50:21.165
Eun-hye.

00:50:21.791 --> 00:50:23.835
She brings misfortune to those around her.

00:50:24.377 --> 00:50:27.255
I hope she gets arrested
for insurance fraud or whatever

00:50:27.964 --> 00:50:29.298
and stays away from my brother.

00:50:31.217 --> 00:50:32.134
We need to talk.

00:50:45.690 --> 00:50:46.816
CHEONGUN FAMILY FIRE FATALITY CASE

00:50:46.899 --> 00:50:48.734
FIRE FATALITY CASE INVESTIGATION REPORT

00:50:54.073 --> 00:50:57.368
At the time, the police concluded
the family committed suicide together.

00:50:58.202 --> 00:51:00.830
POSSIBLE ARSON
RESULTING FROM A SUICIDE ATTEMPT

00:51:05.668 --> 00:51:07.211
I didn't gain anything.

00:51:08.796 --> 00:51:09.964
I only lost.

00:51:13.426 --> 00:51:15.803
Even if it's true
that she survived that tragedy,

00:51:15.887 --> 00:51:17.597
it doesn't excuse her.

00:51:18.514 --> 00:51:19.390
What if…

00:51:20.433 --> 00:51:21.726
it was nothing more

00:51:23.269 --> 00:51:25.062
than a string of bad luck for Han Seol-ah?

00:51:28.649 --> 00:51:32.236
It makes me wonder
if I'm putting her through hell.

00:51:32.862 --> 00:51:35.072
Do you have any other reason
for thinking that?

00:51:35.948 --> 00:51:36.782
Not really.

00:51:37.700 --> 00:51:39.035
It just reminds me of my sister.

00:51:39.911 --> 00:51:40.953
And the truth is,

00:51:41.954 --> 00:51:43.873
everyone has a painful memory
they want to forget.

00:51:44.749 --> 00:51:47.501
Even though I knew
how much pain it'd cause…

00:51:49.921 --> 00:51:50.963
I still pushed her.

00:51:51.672 --> 00:51:53.132
Getting to the truth

00:51:54.300 --> 00:51:56.010
sometimes means being ruthless.

00:51:56.969 --> 00:51:58.012
Do you know what it's like…

00:51:59.680 --> 00:52:01.057
to feel like a scumbag?

00:52:10.858 --> 00:52:12.610
Don't even think about
going there tomorrow.

00:52:13.152 --> 00:52:14.570
Nobody will welcome you.

00:52:15.321 --> 00:52:16.447
It'll be the last time.

00:52:16.530 --> 00:52:17.740
This is so frustrating.

00:52:17.823 --> 00:52:19.283
Do you like torturing yourself
or something?

00:52:19.367 --> 00:52:21.243
Think about yourself first for once.

00:52:21.327 --> 00:52:22.578
I still need to pay my respects.

00:52:28.459 --> 00:52:29.752
TRANQUILIZER

00:52:53.901 --> 00:52:55.861
THE LATE YOON SEUNG-JAE
MEMORIAL TABLET ENSHRINEMENT CEREMONY

00:53:31.939 --> 00:53:33.733
If only he hadn't met you…

00:53:33.816 --> 00:53:37.236
If only he hadn't met you,
my Seung-jae would still be alive!

00:53:38.529 --> 00:53:39.864
He defied his parents,

00:53:39.947 --> 00:53:44.535
got involved with a no-good woman,
and ended up dead!

00:53:48.330 --> 00:53:51.167
My poor baby!

00:53:51.250 --> 00:53:53.085
How dare you come here?!

00:53:53.711 --> 00:53:55.337
How dare you?

00:53:56.422 --> 00:53:58.132
Seung-jae…

00:54:04.805 --> 00:54:06.015
I'd like a word with you.

00:54:08.934 --> 00:54:10.728
My poor Seung-jae…

00:54:16.692 --> 00:54:17.902
INSURANCE POLICY

00:54:19.236 --> 00:54:21.280
Why did my brother
take out a life insurance policy?

00:54:23.783 --> 00:54:25.242
He canceled it soon after,

00:54:25.868 --> 00:54:27.536
but I just don't understand it.

00:54:27.620 --> 00:54:30.664
Why did he spend
200 million won on a policy?

00:54:33.626 --> 00:54:34.668
You know why, don't you?

00:54:37.338 --> 00:54:38.214
No, I don't.

00:54:38.297 --> 00:54:40.800
You were the beneficiary,
so how could you not know?

00:54:43.344 --> 00:54:44.845
I don't know why Seung-jae

00:54:45.429 --> 00:54:47.515
took out an insurance policy.

00:54:49.100 --> 00:54:50.976
Then what did that woman mean?

00:54:53.020 --> 00:54:53.854
Get out.

00:54:53.938 --> 00:54:55.689
Get out right now!

00:54:57.316 --> 00:54:59.652
You'll end up dying at her hands too,

00:55:00.402 --> 00:55:01.320
just like Young-ho.

00:55:01.904 --> 00:55:04.323
Go get some professional help.

00:55:04.406 --> 00:55:05.491
You're not right in the head.

00:55:05.574 --> 00:55:06.951
Do you think I'm joking?

00:55:07.576 --> 00:55:08.661
Get out.

00:55:17.211 --> 00:55:18.045
Are you insane?

00:55:19.713 --> 00:55:21.423
You also took out
a life insurance policy, right?

00:55:25.177 --> 00:55:26.637
You'll regret it.

00:55:27.304 --> 00:55:29.723
She definitely mentioned insurance,

00:55:29.807 --> 00:55:31.684
and in less than two weeks,
the accident happened.

00:55:32.518 --> 00:55:35.020
Seung-jae died,
just like the woman said he would.

00:55:36.438 --> 00:55:38.232
If you don't tell me,

00:55:38.315 --> 00:55:41.694
I'll go to that woman and ask her myself.

00:55:42.653 --> 00:55:43.988
You won't be able to.

00:55:47.783 --> 00:55:48.659
Because that woman…

00:55:50.661 --> 00:55:51.745
also died.

00:55:53.497 --> 00:55:54.415
What?

00:55:56.792 --> 00:55:58.502
The policy was canceled
before the accident,

00:55:59.128 --> 00:56:01.839
and the premium
was returned to his account.

00:56:04.466 --> 00:56:05.426
That's…

00:56:07.136 --> 00:56:08.262
all I know.

00:56:14.977 --> 00:56:16.228
Who exactly are you?

00:56:17.813 --> 00:56:18.772
I had my suspicions,

00:56:20.399 --> 00:56:22.985
but this must be why
the SIU investigator kept calling.

00:56:25.279 --> 00:56:26.363
You killed them, didn't you?

00:56:27.114 --> 00:56:29.575
You're the one who killed Seung-jae
and that woman, aren't you?!

00:56:30.659 --> 00:56:31.994
Tell me!

00:56:32.494 --> 00:56:33.370
Who are you?

00:56:34.038 --> 00:56:35.789
I'm the SIU investigator.

00:56:48.302 --> 00:56:50.971
THE LATE YOON SEUNG-JAE

00:58:06.213 --> 00:58:08.757
I wonder how far
a string of bad luck can go.

00:58:11.719 --> 00:58:12.803
A work colleague.

00:58:13.595 --> 00:58:14.596
A significant other.

00:58:18.475 --> 00:58:20.060
And even your parents.

00:58:25.524 --> 00:58:27.318
Did you really just lose everything

00:58:28.402 --> 00:58:29.987
and have nothing to do with their deaths?

00:58:38.329 --> 00:58:39.330
Do you still think…

00:58:41.832 --> 00:58:43.709
I killed someone?

00:58:47.963 --> 00:58:48.797
I suppose…

00:58:51.133 --> 00:58:53.052
you wouldn't believe a word I say.

00:59:25.000 --> 00:59:26.335
What are you doing? Are you insane?!

00:59:27.503 --> 00:59:29.254
All I have to do is disappear.

00:59:29.338 --> 00:59:30.964
Then it'll all be over!

00:59:31.548 --> 00:59:32.591
What?

00:59:32.674 --> 00:59:34.259
I don't care!

00:59:35.177 --> 00:59:38.472
I want to die! Why are you stopping me?

00:59:40.682 --> 00:59:41.850
Why are you doing this to me?

00:59:42.601 --> 00:59:43.852
What do you want to know?

00:59:44.895 --> 00:59:46.980
What more do you want to know?

00:59:48.941 --> 00:59:49.817
You.

00:59:51.110 --> 00:59:52.528
I want to know more about you.

00:59:54.405 --> 00:59:56.824
I want to know about the person
who could die right now and not care!

01:00:19.179 --> 01:00:21.723
SPECIAL THANKS TO YOON JONGHUN
FOR HIS APPEARANCE

01:00:43.579 --> 01:00:44.580
Obsessed?

01:00:45.038 --> 01:00:46.999
I just want to know the truth.

01:00:48.417 --> 01:00:49.418
Did you do it on purpose?

01:00:50.002 --> 01:00:51.753
You're suspicious,
but you have no evidence.

01:00:51.837 --> 01:00:53.589
Was it really necessary
to get on your knees?

01:00:53.672 --> 01:00:56.842
Do you think money
will make that pain go away?

01:00:57.551 --> 01:00:59.720
These three men
follow the exact same pattern.

01:00:59.803 --> 01:01:00.762
Can you really call it a coincidence?

01:01:01.346 --> 01:01:02.806
There was someone else.

01:01:02.890 --> 01:01:03.974
Are you saying

01:01:04.057 --> 01:01:06.185
someone deliberately targeted
Han Seol-ah's men and killed them?

01:01:06.894 --> 01:01:08.687
If the culprit thinks I'm your man…

01:01:11.273 --> 01:01:12.524
I'll either die…

01:01:14.234 --> 01:01:15.819
or find out who the real culprit is.

01:01:17.029 --> 01:01:19.031
Subtitle: Jenny Kim